[00:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '3 months ago, we published our launch video.&nbsp; From the outside, you haven\'t maybe seen a lot,&nbsp;&nbsp; but we have been building non-stop. It\'s been&nbsp; about 3 months since we shown you Warmwind OS,&nbsp;&nbsp; and so far we had a lot of positive feedback,&nbsp; and it\'s about time that we give you a quick&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'preview and update on the new version, warmwind Beta V2. Also, till the end of the video,&nbsp;&nbsp; I will definitely tell you how you will get access&nbsp; to the next rollout stage. When we take a look at&nbsp;&nbsp; the product, everything feels pretty familiar. Not&nbsp; a lot of things changed. It\'s just a minor update.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'But still, we think these changes were necessary&nbsp; with the feedback of our users to make the product&nbsp;&nbsp; feel even greater. First thing we changed&nbsp; um is how you should think about the space.&nbsp;&nbsp; What we found is that people like to give a lot&nbsp; of smaller task over day and typically spaces&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'only have to be active for a few minutes or a&nbsp; few hours a day but not 24/7. This typically&nbsp;&nbsp; broke the bank for many users because you wanted&nbsp; to split different use cases across multiple&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'spaces. With the new architecture, you can and&nbsp; you even should. We found when you take your&nbsp;&nbsp; tasks and split them across multiple spaces, the&nbsp; quality of the output will improve significantly.&nbsp;&nbsp; So from now on we have a new payment structure&nbsp; in place and a new architecture that will allow&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you to create much more spaces with um smaller&nbsp; individual tasks. When we create a new space and&nbsp;&nbsp; let\'s just install I don\'t know Chrome and we&nbsp; give it a first task something like get me the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stock price of Apple. You will see that at the&nbsp; beginning spaces typically tend to be quite slow&nbsp;&nbsp; and you see the space starts thinking and now&nbsp; it\'s counting up like seconds over seconds over&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'seconds. You can also see the next feature which&nbsp; I will come to in a minute which is the worklist&nbsp;&nbsp; here at the sidebar. We found that many users&nbsp; greatly prefer quality of output versus speed&nbsp;&nbsp; of output. What you can see here is a new model&nbsp; we created. We went back to the drawing board and&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really put emphasis on accuracy of output versus&nbsp; only speed. But because we had this opportunity&nbsp;&nbsp; to rethink the whole architecture from this point&nbsp; of view, we created a model which can really learn&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'on its task. So while it\'s pretty slow at the&nbsp; beginning, it will get faster and faster while&nbsp;&nbsp; it\'s growing with its tasks. where when you have&nbsp; a list task with extracting data from thousands of&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'rows of PDF or whatever, you will see that&nbsp; a model will start quite slowly sometimes a&nbsp;&nbsp; click will take 10 seconds but over time the&nbsp; speed will increase drastically so it\'s just&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like muscle memory the model is learning on the&nbsp; job and after a few minutes you will see that&nbsp;&nbsp; that the speed increases 10 or 20x from the&nbsp; base speed while keeping high accuracy. So,&nbsp;&nbsp; as we\'ve already seen at the sidebar, that\'s what&nbsp; we call our visor. Like, it\'s a head-up display.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It\'s always inside the view, but it never gets&nbsp; into your way. It typically shows you where the&nbsp;&nbsp; AI currently is in its task. And now you can see&nbsp; it went all the way back to the top because it&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'finished the task. And I could tell it like do the&nbsp; same thing again. I will not do this right now.&nbsp;&nbsp; So when we come over to our sidebar visor, we&nbsp; will see that it will expand and show us all the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'different steps the model takes to reach our goal.&nbsp; This was a very easy task but with more complex&nbsp;&nbsp; workflows this will come in very handy. So when&nbsp; we come over here we see this worklist and this&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'worklist can be edited in two ways. Number one&nbsp; I can just go in and tell it what to do. So for&nbsp;&nbsp; example here I see um the stock price was searched&nbsp; up in euro. Maybe I want US dollar. Then I can say&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'um get me the get me the price in USD not euro&nbsp; um for example um but let\'s remove it there&nbsp;&nbsp; and we can go down here and say um not not euro&nbsp; please do USD always. And now we can see when we&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'come over to the worklist again, it updated the&nbsp; worklist and now it shows use US dollar. That\'s&nbsp;&nbsp; how easy it is to use the worklist. And when I&nbsp; change my mind and maybe I don\'t really want to&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'type a lot in the chat and I can just go in here&nbsp; and change it back to well, let\'s use euro. And&nbsp;&nbsp; now that that\'s working, we can just go over&nbsp; to the next space and I will show you a new&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'addition to the teaching mode. All of us really&nbsp; loved the teaching mode and I think you will too.&nbsp;&nbsp; There\'s no easier way to create an automation&nbsp; than just showing the AI what you want it to&nbsp;&nbsp; do. And with teaching mode, you can just take over&nbsp; control of the cursor and talk the model through&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your reasoning process. This really enables the&nbsp; model to get a real deep understanding of your&nbsp;&nbsp; thinking and why you do certain things the way&nbsp; you\'re doing them. And we found there are just&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'some situations where it\'s not really possible to&nbsp; talk to your computer. Maybe you\'re in a library,&nbsp;&nbsp; maybe you\'re in a train, maybe you\'re in a cafe.&nbsp; That\'s why we introduce text input. I personally&nbsp;&nbsp; call it cursor chat. You click continue. So when&nbsp; I take over control of the cursor before I always&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just could talk to the computer. So this is to&nbsp; be honest still my preferred method but it\'s just&nbsp;&nbsp; not always possible. So this is the new way. You&nbsp; just take the cursor and click wherever you want.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And now there\'s an input opening up. And you can&nbsp; just describe why the model should click here.&nbsp;&nbsp; Um yeah, and if you do this and go through&nbsp; your task, um you will then just hit finish&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and a new worklist will be created by whatever&nbsp; you show in the model. Overall, V2 is just much&nbsp;&nbsp; more stable and feels much more natural to use.&nbsp; Also, the AI will really pick up on your goals&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and you\'re not forced to write these super long&nbsp; prompts. Still, this is a technical preview and&nbsp;&nbsp;'
